    • Method Detail

      • validateScopedName

        public static void validateScopedName(java.lang.String name)
        Validate that a scoped object name is valid. Currently, the only type of name that may be scoped with the ':' character is an algorithm name.
        Parameters:
        name - The name to check
        Throws:
        InvalidNameException - when the name is invalid

      • validateUnscopedName

        public static void validateUnscopedName(java.lang.String name)
        Validate that an unscoped object name is valid. Framework names and algorithm names for algorithms built in to a plugin are subject to this check.
        Parameters:
        name - The name to check
        Throws:
        InvalidNameException - when the name is invalid

      • validateUnscopedName

        public static void validateUnscopedName(java.lang.String name,
                                        int maxLength)
        Validate that an unscoped object name is valid. This is useful for objects other than algorithms and frameworks which may have different name length limits.
        Parameters:
        name - The name to check
        maxLength - The maximum length of the object name
        Throws:
        InvalidNameException - when the name is invalid
